> [DBSC] Make it easier to test binding keys on Linux and Mac

>

> //crypto currently has an UnexportableKeyProvider support on Windows

>

> implementation of an UnexportableKeyProvider behind a feature flag. This

> feature flag is expected to never be shipped to end users.

entry.content:
HWUI passes clip rect in a OutputSurface space that webview expected to

handle and never draw outside. But it's not necessarily content clip

rect, e.g hwui limits that rect for damage and it can different every

time even if never changed webcontents or webview position on screen.



This is problematic when we start clipping overlays using that rect.



This CL adds Display::SetOutputSurfaceClipRect function that allows

to specify limitation that is supposed to be applied for draw, but

nothing else.

entry.title: Enable and disable MSBB on history opt-in changes
entry.content:
This CL changes the way sync opt-in affects MSBB (aka in code as

URL-keyed data collection) for clients that have

`kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos` feature flag enabled. It does

not affect clients that are not in this experiment group.



For clients in this experiment, the CL enables and disables MSBB every

time user enables or disables history sync. This differs compared to the

previous implementation that relied on the sync opt-in in.



In the new implementation, `UnifiedConsentService` monitors all

changes to history opt-in and updates the state of the

UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled preference accordingly, so an

explicit call from the History opt-in UI is not needed anymore. This

is considered safe as history sync will be enabled only once the user

clicks "Yes" from the history opt-in screen and when the user toggles

the history toggle from the account settings.

entry.title: exo: Allocate surface id if not when pixel host window bounds changed
entry.content:
This CL explicitly allocates viz::LocalSurfaceId when the pixel bounds

of host window is updated but id is not updated.



We need to always allocate local surface id when pixel coordinates host

window bounds has changed.

- Scaled bounds is not changed: Allocated by crrev.com/c/4639542

- Scaled size is changed: Allocated by host_window_->SetBounds

- Scaled size is not changed, but origin is changed: NOT addressed



This change is required to address the case where scaled bounds is

changed but not the size since SetLocalSurfaceId is triggered by
